  "informal_statement": "If f : alpha -> beta and g : beta -> gamma are both surjective functions, then their composition g . f : alpha -> gamma is surjective.",
  "informal_proof_idea": "Take any target c : gamma. Surjectivity of g gives b : beta with g b = c. Surjectivity of f gives a : alpha with f a = b. Then (g . f) a = g (f a) = g b = c, so a witnesses surjectivity of g . f at c.",
  "formal_statement_pp": "theorem surjective_comp : ∀ {α β γ : Type} (f : α → β) (g : β → γ), Function.Surjective f → Function.Surjective g → Function.Surjective (g ∘ f)",
